{"abstract": "https://confengine.com/agile-india-2016/proposal/1792", "description": "In this highly engaging workshop attendees will experience estimating, planning and delivering a new product and product features. The uncertainty in value and costs will be resolved through rolling dice based on the stories that the team selects and prioritizes.   The teams will run through 3 iterations of story cost, value estimation, and product feature delivery. Points will be scored for delivering product features and meeting release and iteration commitments.\n\nDealing with uncertainty is one of the largest challenges that teams face. The simulation aims to have levels of uncertainty in value and delivery that are commensurate with those found in software development. Some of the key tools for dealing with uncertainty are integrated into the simulation.\n\nAttendees will come away with a better understanding of the challenges of working with uncertainty in software projects, and will learn some of the tools that are at their disposal for managing this uncertainty.", "event": {"name": "Agile India 2016", "nickname": "agile-india-2016", "twitter": "agileindia", "url": "http://2016.agileindia.org/"}, "favorite": "0", "file_date": "2016-12-03", "filename": "the-value-uncertainty-game-by-chris-edwards-sean-dunn", "length": "47:19", "likes": "0", "recorded": "2016-03-14", "short_description": "In this highly engaging workshop attendees will experience estimating, planning and delivering a new product and product feature", "speaker_twitters": " @chrisedwardsuk @SeanDunn10", "speakers": {"chris-edwards": {"episodes": [], "hosting": [], "info": {"country": "Canada", "home": "http://chrisedwardsuk.blogspot.com/", "name": "Chris Edwards", "twitter": "chrisedwardsuk"}, "videos": [{"event": {"name": "Agile India 2016", "nickname": "agile-india-2016", "twitter": "agileindia", "url": "http://2016.agileindia.org/"}, "filename": "7-sins-of-scrum-and-other-agile-antipatterns-by-sean-dunn-chri